Originally ripped by Terminal Escape, posted on December 21, 2015 Description from Terminal Escape:
I'm pretty sure that you requested a bulldozer, right? A collection of sounds with enough power to yank up your complacency at the roots? Well, here's a juggernaut from Victoria, BC that ought to do the trick: THICK SKULL. A few bits from mid '00s heavy North American crust, the tiniest sprinkling of chaotic emotional hardcore and a hint of black metal, but mostly just desperate sounding and devastating hardcore. For those of you who would like to start your week with power. THICK SKULL
